definitions.definition: To completely remove , get rid of , put an end to.
To render (a facility) unusable, to destroy it; to disable (a soldier), make them unable to fight (typically but not necessarily by killing)

examples: a ruthless mobster who eliminated his enemies

definitions.definition: To exclude (from investigation or from further competition).
examples: Bill was eliminated as a suspect when the police interviewed witnesses.
John was eliminated as a contestant when it was found he had gained, rather than lost, weight.

definitions.definition: To record amounts in a consolidation statement to remove the effects of inter-company transactions.

main_definition: ( transitive ) To completely remove , get rid of , put an end to.
secondary_definitions: ( transitive , military ) To render (a facility) unusable, to destroy it; to disable (a soldier), make them unable to fight (typically but not necessarily by killing)
( transitive , slang ) To kill (a person or animal).
( transitive ) To exclude (from investigation or from further competition).
( accounting ) To record amounts in a consolidation statement to remove the effects of inter-company transactions.
